<HEADING>Recommended reading

<LIST>

Also worthy of note are the O'Reilly 'nutshell' handbooks, which cover
everything from '<b>When You Can't Find Your UNIX System Administrator</b>' to
the '<b>X Toolkit Intrinsics Reference Manual</b>'.
See <a href="http://unix.oreilly.com/">unix.oreilly.com</a> for full listing.

<p>
If you have comments on any of the above, or more references that could be
added to the above list, please <a href="../Misc/feedback.html">contact us</a>.
</p>

<p>
<blockquote>
"The best book on programming for the layman is `Alice in Wonderland';
but that's because it's the best book on anything for the layman."
</blockquote>
</p>

<SECTION>For Users

<ENTRY>0-07-025492-3 A Student's Guide to Unix, Second Edition
Author: Harley Hahn<br>
Publication: McGraw-Hill, 1996 (ISBN 0-07-025492-3)<br>
Designed to be a reference and an educational resource, the book aims to
describe all the basic skills involved as well as tips, hints, and techniques.

<ENTRY>1-56592-104-6 When You Can't Find Your UNIX System Administrator
Author: Linda Mui<br>
Publication: O'Reilly, 1995. (ISBN 1-56592-104-6)<br>
A slim volume, but to quote: <em>"The goal of this book is not to make
you a guru in your own right. The goal of this book is to get you back
to the job you'd rather be doing."</em> <a
href="http://www.oreilly.com/catalog/usa/">More details</a>.

<ENTRY>4881356186 NetBSD/mac68k primer<em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Fumio Kamiyama<br>
Publication: Shoeisha<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<SECTION>Administering a system

<ENTRY>0-13-151051-7 UNIX System Administration Handbook, Second Edition
Authors: Evi Nemeth, Garth Snyder, Scott Seebass, and Trent R. Hein<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall, 1995. (ISBN 0-13-151051-7)<br>
Many enthusiastic endorsements from sysadmins. <a
href="http://www.admin.com/">More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-8053-7565-1 A Practical Guide to the Unix System, Third Edition
Author: Mark Sobell<br>
Publication: Addison Wesley, 1995. (ISBN 0-8053-7565-1)<br>
Recommended as a student text.  <a
href="http://cseng.aw.com/bookdetail.qry?ISBN=0-8053-7565-1&ptype=0">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>3-932311-31-0 BSD mit Methode <em>(German language)</em>
Authors: M. Schulze, Dr. B. R&ouml;hrig, M. H&ouml;lzer et al.<br>
Publication: C&L Computer&Literatur, 1998 (ISBN 3-932311-31-0)<br>
853 pages and 2 CD-ROMs, DM 98.-/&Ouml;s 715,-<br>
Introduces the beginner to installation, administration and usage of
the free BSD versions, X11, LaTeX, PERL, and internet services.
With 2 CDs containing (among others) NetBSD-1.3.2, KDE 1.0 and other
software packages for Intel CPUs.
<a href="http://www.cul.de/buecher/bsd.html">More details</a>.

<ENTRY>4881357824 NetBSD/mac68k handbook <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Fumio Kamiyama<br>
Publication: Shoeisha<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<ENTRY>4816326448 NetBSD/mac68k networking guide <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Hiroyuki Hasegawa<br>
Publication: Natsume publishing<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<ENTRY>4879668834 NetBSD for beginners: volume on network server <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Tadaomi Miyazaki<br>
Publication: Shuwa System Inc.<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<ENTRY>4073909177 MkLinux DR3/NetBSD 1.3.2 internet server configuration primer <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Top Management Service<br>
Publication: Locus<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<ENTRY>4896212169 NetBSD/mac68k beginner's bible <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Fems<br>
Publication: Spike<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<ENTRY>4073907972 MkLinux DR3/NetBSD 1.3.2 server configuration primer <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Author: Top Management Service<br>
Publication: Locus<br>
(awaiting for reviews)

<SECTION>Programming

<ENTRY>0-201-54979-4 The Design and Implementation of the 4.4 BSD Operating System
Authors: Marshall Kirk McKusick, Keith Bostic, Michael J. Karels,
John S. Quarterman<br>
Publication: Addison Wesley, 1996. (ISBN 0-201-54979-4)<br>
The definitive work on 4.4 BSD internals. A must for any kernel programmer.
<a href="http://cseng.aw.com/bookdetail.qry?ISBN=0-201-54979-4&ptype=0">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-201-56317-7 Advanced Programming in the Unix Environment
Author: W. Richard Stevens<br>
Publication: Addison Wesley, 1993. (ISBN 0-201-56317-7).<br>
<a href="http://cseng.awl.com/bookdetail.qry?ISBN=0-201-56317-7&ptype=0">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-13-101908-2 Unix Internals: The New Frontiers
Author: Uresh Vahalia<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall, 1995. (ISBN 0-13-101908-2)<br>
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/books/esm_0131019082.html">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-13-937681-x The UNIX (R) Programming Environment, First Edition
Authors: Brian W. Kernighan, Rob Pike<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall, 1984. (ISBN 0-13-937681-X)<br>
The original UNIX programming environment and philosophy.
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/allbooks/esm_013937681X.html">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-13-326224-3 C: A Reference Manual, Fourth Edition
Authors: Samuel P. Harbison, Guy L. Steele<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall, 1995. (ISBN 0-13-326224-3)<br>
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/books/esm_0133262243.html">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-13-110362-8 C Programming Language, Second Edition
Authors: Brian Kernighan, Dennis Ritchie<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall, 1989. (ISBN 0-13-110362-8)<br>
The (updated) original text on C. Not the easiest read, but pretty much
from the original source.
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/books/ptr_0131103628.html">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>4-89052-808-3 X68k Programming Series (#4) <em>(Japanese language)</em>
Authors: NetBSD/X68k committee<br>
Publication: SOFTBANK (ISBN 4-89052-808-3 C0055)<br>
<a href="http://www.rd.cc.kshosen.ac.jp/~kamahara/NetBSD-X680x0/Ports/x68k/book.html">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-201-63354-x TCP/IP Illustrated, Vol. 2
Authors: Gary R. Wright, W. Richard Stevens<br>
Publication: Addison Wesley, 1995 (ISBN 0-201-63354-X)<br>
A technical breakdown of the 4.4BSD networking implementation.
<a href="http://cseng.aw.com/bookdetail.qry?ISBN=0-201-63354-X&ptype=0">
More details</a>.

<ENTRY>0-13-081081-9 UNIX Network Programming (Volumes 1 and 2), Second Edition
Author: W. Richard Stevens<br>
Publication: Prentice-Hall 1997 (ISBN 0-13-490012-X),
			    1998 (ISBN 0-13-081081-9)<br>
The classic UNIX network programming guide, now completely updated.<br>
More details:
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/allbooks/ptr_013490012X.html">Vol1</a>,
<a href="http://www.prenhall.com/allbooks/ptr_0130810819.html">Vol2</a>.

</LIST>

